There was a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hangul#Linear_Hangul" class="postlink">failed movement to restructure hangul sequentially</a> like every other alphabet. A compromise is the UnJamo fonts (seen <a href="http://www.wazu.jp/gallery/Fonts_Korean.html" class="postlink">here</a> and on the following page), which make each consonant letter a fixed size rather than the traditional method of stretching each syllable to fit a square.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun May 07, 2017 7:45 am</p><hr />
